## Methodology

### Phase 1 — Data Foundation
- Loaded and cleaned 9,789 FMCG transactions
- Converted Order Date to datetime index
- Calculated Lead Time Days (mean 3.96 days, std 1.75 days)
- Removed 11 null rows (Postal Code) — 9,789 clean records

### Phase 2 — Exploratory Data Analysis
- Monthly sales trend with 3-month rolling average
- Category breakdown — Technology $825K, Furniture $723K,
  Office Supplies $703K
- Sub-category SKU level demand view — Phones and Chairs top 2
- Seasonality decomposition — trend, seasonal, residual components
- Regional demand distribution — West 31.5%, East 29.3%
- Sub-category x Region heatmap — Chairs dominate West ($100,023)

### Phase 3 — ABC/XYZ Segmentation
- ABC: Revenue contribution (A=70%, B=20%, C=10%)
- XYZ: Coefficient of variation (X<0.5, Y=0.5-1.0, Z>1.0)
- 17 sub-categories classified across 6 demand segments
- Model assignment framework per segment

### Phase 4 — External Variables (Demand Sensing)
- US public holidays — 373 orders on holiday dates identified
- Month, quarter, is_Q4, is_month_end, day_of_week features
- Enriched feature matrix for Prophet and XGBoost

### Phase 5 — Excel Baseline Models
- Naive 3-Month Moving Average — MAPE 50.8%
- Exponential Smoothing (alpha=0.3) — MAPE 46.71%
- Weighted Moving Average (50/30/20) — MAPE 48.66%
- Year-over-Year Growth (20.76% rate) — MAPE 27.73%
- Seasonal Index — MAPE 26.74%
- Linear Trend + Seasonal — MAPE 19.0% (Excel winner)

### Phase 6 — Python Statistical and ML Models
- Holt-Winters (additive trend + seasonal) — MAPE 17.40%
- SARIMA (1,1,1)(1,1,1)12 — MAPE 27.05%
- Prophet with US holiday regressors — MAPE 15.79% (overall winner)
- XGBoost — tested and documented (insufficient training data)

### Phase 7 — SKU Level Forecasting
- Prophet forecast for Phones (AY segment) — MAPE 35.96%
- Prophet forecast for Chairs (AY segment) — MAPE 48.71%
- Croston's method for Copiers (BZ, CV=1.63) — MAE $4,510
- Croston vs Prophet comparison on intermittent demand SKU

### Phase 8 — Safety Stock Optimisation
- Safety Stock = Z x sigma x sqrt(Lead Time)
- Z = 1.65 (95% service level)
- Compared Naive MA vs Holt-Winters vs Prophet
- $470,146 annual holding cost saving identified

### Phase 9 — S&OP Scenario Planning
- Three scenarios: Pessimistic (-15%), Base, Optimistic (+15%)
- November 2018 demand shock identified — exceeded optimistic by 14%
- Fan chart aligned with S&OP consensus meeting format

