## Key Business Findings

**1. Prophet beats every Excel method by minimum 3 MAPE points**
Holiday-aware ML forecasting outperforms even the best
statistical Excel approach (Linear Trend + Seasonal 19%).

**2. Best Excel model beats Naive by 63%**
Linear Trend + Seasonal demonstrates that even without ML
structured statistical methods add significant value.

**3. XGBoost needs more data**
With only 36 months of training data XGBoost underperformed.
In production with 3+ years of daily SKU data it would be
the recommended model.

**4. SKU level forecasting is harder than aggregate**
Phones MAPE 35.96% vs aggregate 15.79% — random errors cancel
at aggregate level. Intermittent demand SKUs (Copiers CV=1.63)
require Croston's method not standard time series models.

**5. November demand shock exceeded all scenarios**
Actual $117,938 vs optimistic scenario $103,000 — proving
that promotional data is required to forecast extreme peaks.

